{{Infobox artwork | image_file = File:Raphaelle Peale - Still Life with Cake (1818).jpg | caption = | alt = | image_size = | title =Still Life with Cake | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_title_2 = | artist = [[Raphaelle Peale]] | subject = | year = 1818 | material = Oil on canvas | height_metric = 27.3 | width_metric = | length_metric = 38.7 | diameter_metric = | city = [[New York City]] | museum = [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]] | accession = 59.166 }} '''''Still Life with Cake''''' is an early 19th century still life painting by [[Raphaelle Peale]]. Done in oil on canvas, the painting is in the collection of the [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/11737|title=metmuseum.org|website=www.metmuseum.org|access-date=2018-09-09}}</ref>
